Pandoc
  Meta { unMeta = fromList [] }
  [ Header
      2
      ( "and-it-came-to-pass-in-the-course-of-those-many-days"
      , [ "Myheading2" ]
      , []
      )
      [ Str
          "159. And It Came to Pass in the Course of Those Many Days"
      ]
  , Para [ Str "I heard" ]
  , Para
      [ Str
          "\8220And it came to pass in the course of those many days that the king of Egypt died; and the children of Israel sighed by reason of the bondage, and they cried, and their cry came up unto God by reason of the bondage. And God heard their groaning\8221 (Exodus 2:23-4). This means that they suffered so much that they could not bear it any longer. And they so pleaded with prayer, that \8220their cry came up unto God.\8221"
      ]
  , Para
      [ Str
          "But we can see that they were saying, \8220Would that we had\8230 when we sat by the flesh-pots, when we did eat bread to the full.\8221 And they also said, \8220We remember the fish, which we would eat in Egypt for naught; the cucumbers, and the melons, and the leeks, and the onions, and the garlic.\8221"
      ]
  , Para
      [ Str
          "The thing is that, indeed, they were very fond of the work in Egypt. This is the meaning of \8220But mingled themselves with the nations, and learned their works.\8221 It means that if Israel are under the dominion of a certain nation, that nation controls them and they cannot retire from their dominion. Thus, they tasted sufficient flavor in that work and could not be redeemed."
      ]
  , Para
      [ Str
          "So what did the Creator do? \8220The king of Egypt died,\8221 meaning they had lost this servitude. Thus they could no longer work; they understood that if there is no perfection of the "
      , Emph [ Str "Mochin" ]
      , Str
          ", the servitude is also incomplete. Hence, \8220and the children of Israel sighed by reason of the bondage.\8221 The work means that they did not suffice for the work, that they had no liveliness in the servitude."
      ]
  , Para
      [ Str
          "This is the meaning of \8220the king of Egypt died,\8221 that all the dominations of the king of Egypt, which he was providing for and nourishing, had died. This is why they had room for prayer. And they were immediately salvaged. And afterwards, when they walked in the desert and came to a state of "
      , Emph [ Str "Katnut" ]
      , Str
          " (smallness), they craved the servitude that they had had prior to the death of the king of Egypt."
      ]
  ]
